<article id="post-2" class="post-2 page type-page status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry hidetitle">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">WELCOME TO FIREFLY</h1>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	<div class="post-thumbnail">
		<img width="1200" height="188"   alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" data-srcset="https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-1200x188.jpg 1200w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-400x63.jpg 400w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-300x47.jpg 300w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-768x120.jpg 768w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-1024x160.jpg 1024w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-480x75.jpg 480w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner.jpg 1280w"  data-src="https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-1200x188.jpg" data-sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 60vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" /><noscript><img width="1200" height="188" src="https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-1200x188.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-1200x188.jpg 1200w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-400x63.jpg 400w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-300x47.jpg 300w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-768x120.jpg 768w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-1024x160.jpg 1024w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner-480x75.jpg 480w, https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Firefly-homepage-banner.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 60vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /></noscript>	</div><!-- .post-thumbnail -->

	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<div id="main">
<h1>GLOWING, GLOWING, GONE.</h1>
<p><strong>Fireflies light up our yards on hot summer nights, and many of us have cherished memories of them. But fireflies are disappearing all over the country—and all over the world. </strong></p>
<h2>A resource for firefly lovers—and scientists</h2>
<p>Firefly Conservation &amp; Research is an organization with two missions: to support firefly research and conservation, and to spread the message that fireflies need our help.</p>
<div id="envira-gallery-wrap-858" class="envira-gallery-wrap envira-gallery-theme-base envira-lightbox-theme-base_dark" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageGallery"><div data-row-height="" data-justified-margins="" data-gallery-theme="" id="envira-gallery-858" class="envira-gallery-public  envira-gallery-3-columns envira-clear" data-envira-columns="3"><div id="envira-gallery-item-859" class="envira-gallery-item enviratope-item envira-gallery-item-1" style="padding-left: 5px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-right: 5px;"  itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><div class="envira-gallery-item-inner"><div class="envira-gallery-position-overlay  envira-gallery-top-left"></div><div class="envira-gallery-position-overlay  envira-gallery-top-right"></div><div class="envira-gallery-position-overlay  envira-gallery-bottom-left"></div><div class="envira-gallery-position-overlay  envira-gallery-bottom-right"></div><a  href="https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/photinus-firefly-flying-away-disappearing.jpg" class="envira-gallery-858 envira-gallery-link " rel="enviragallery858" title="Photinus firefly flashing" data-envira-caption="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.firefly.org/why-are-fireflies-disappearing.html&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Why Are Fireflies Disappearing?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Like Fourth-of-July fireworks, cool swims on hot days, and lazy vacations, fireflies are a sign of summer. Many of us have cherished memories of spotting and catching them during warm summer evenings and running through fields that sparkled as if strewn with stars. But there are signs our kids may not grow up with the same firefly memories we had. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.firefly.org/why-are-fireflies-disappearing.html&quot;&gt;Learn More&lt;/a&gt;" data-envira-lightbox-caption="Photinus firefly flashing" data-envira-retina="" data-thumbnail="https://www.firefly.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/photinus-firefly-flying-away-disappearing-150x100_c.jpg" data-mobile-thumbnail="h